1
00:01:48,388 --> 00:01:51,068
You three seem close, so how long
have you been traveling together?

2
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:58,731
My travels with Mistress Frieren began
four years ago, but I've known her longer.

3
00:01:59,731 --> 00:02:01,092
It's been about a year for me.

4
00:02:04,613 --> 00:02:05,613
Makes sense.

5
00:02:10,835 --> 00:02:13,715
You know, there's still
something this party lacks.

6
00:02:13,915 --> 00:02:14,915
What?

7
00:02:15,036 --> 00:02:16,036
Wanna take a guess?

8
00:02:16,647 --> 00:02:21,628
Let's see... We've got our front liner, a
decent priest, and a near surplus of mages.

9
00:02:22,189 --> 00:02:23,189
Could you mean a thief?

10
00:02:23,709 --> 00:02:26,530
Someone to out-swindle the
mimic she's always falling for?

11
00:02:30,731 --> 00:02:33,892
When it comes to treasure chests,
the reward always outweighs the risk.

12
00:02:34,692 --> 00:02:35,692
No.

13
00:02:36,592 --> 00:02:38,553
What we lack is something even more vital.

14
00:02:39,965 --> 00:02:41,665
And that's a nice-looking older lady!

15
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:44,462
Most parties won't even leave
town until they've found a broad!

16
00:02:44,486 --> 00:02:46,807
That's the way, or else
you're vixenless like us!

17
00:02:48,007 --> 00:02:49,007
Is that right?

18
00:02:50,248 --> 00:02:51,988
Come on, don't forget about Frieren.

19
00:02:52,448 --> 00:02:54,869
She's more of an elderly child than a lady.

20
00:02:55,309 --> 00:02:56,549
He looks so distraught.

21
00:02:56,910 --> 00:02:57,910
My apologies.

22
00:02:59,610 --> 00:02:59,690
Hey!

23
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:02,011
You can finally see the next village!

24
00:03:20,107 --> 00:03:21,107
They're still breathing.

25
00:03:21,528 --> 00:03:23,149
Yeah, same here.

26
00:03:24,469 --> 00:03:25,870
What's the deal with this place?

27
00:03:26,090 --> 00:03:27,291
Why'd they all fall asleep?

28
00:03:30,272 --> 00:03:32,190
I say we move along to the next village.

29
00:03:32,214 --> 00:03:33,514
This smells like trouble.

30
00:03:33,974 --> 00:03:35,956
Even for you, that's cold.

31
00:03:36,636 --> 00:03:37,716
I was only teasing.

32
00:03:39,658 --> 00:03:40,658
A curse, no doubt.

33
00:03:41,238 --> 00:03:42,238
I thought as much.

34
00:03:42,519 --> 00:03:43,519
What a headache.

35
00:03:45,020 --> 00:03:47,642
This may sound dumb,
but what even is a curse?

36
00:03:48,345 --> 00:03:54,548
Among the spells utilized by monsters and demons are
those that put people to sleep or turn them into stone.

37
00:03:55,369 --> 00:04:01,072
Those whose mysteries humankind is yet to unravel are
what we call curses, a placeholder for the unknown.

38
00:04:02,852 --> 00:04:06,614
Humanity's magic can't explain the
principles behind them or how to lift them.

39
00:04:07,775 --> 00:04:10,095
Does that mean it's already
too late to save these people?

40
00:04:10,576 --> 00:04:13,618
It is only the magic of man
that faces such an impasse.

41
00:04:14,658 --> 00:04:17,640
The magic of the goddess that
priests use is a different story.

42
00:04:18,953 --> 00:04:21,975
Dispelling curses has long
been the business of the clergy.

43
00:04:23,516 --> 00:04:25,617
Well, Sein, suppose you can help them?

44
00:04:26,938 --> 00:04:27,938
Don't rush me.

45
00:04:28,239 --> 00:04:30,520
I need to determine the
type and source of this thing.

46
00:04:34,923 --> 00:04:36,324
I thought magic was magic.

47
00:04:36,704 --> 00:04:38,285
What makes the goddesses so unique?

48
00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:42,207
The magic of the goddess is
recorded in holy scriptures, you see.

49
00:04:42,848 --> 00:04:44,589
Only those who own them can wield it.

50
00:04:45,855 --> 00:04:49,598
Much like the demon's magic, the principles
behind the bulk of it aren't understood.

51
00:04:50,938 --> 00:04:53,240
So it's not the sort of
thing that holds my interest.

52
00:04:55,101 --> 00:04:59,184
That, and it's incredibly difficult to use
unless you're born with a certain knack.

53
00:05:00,605 --> 00:05:04,287
That same predisposition comes
with an increased resistance to curses.

54
00:05:05,148 --> 00:05:07,810
It's what the faithful bunch
call the blessing of the goddess.

55
00:05:08,647 --> 00:05:11,489
And it's the reason this sleepy
spell won't affect our priest.

56
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:16,032
So not even a mage at your level
can really defend against curses?

57
00:05:16,372 --> 00:05:19,454
We mages can't detect them,
let alone defend against them.

58
00:05:20,254 --> 00:05:22,896
Though I do feel that I am
under attack for some reason.

59
00:05:23,276 --> 00:05:26,618
So I can conclude that this place
is still under the power of the curse.

60
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:28,659
My soul feels itchy.

61
00:05:28,699 --> 00:05:32,922
You can't just say scary things like that and
expect me not to turn into a giant sniveling baby!

62
00:05:35,143 --> 00:05:37,665
This isn't a low-grade everyday
spell we're dealing with here.

63
00:05:38,165 --> 00:05:39,465
Can you lift it or can't you?

64
00:05:40,266 --> 00:05:41,426
I would need the right tools.

65
00:05:41,926 --> 00:05:46,348
Honestly, it might be easier to take
out the source than to treat its symptoms.

66
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:50,309
It's coming from a monster,
and I know where it is.

67
00:05:51,049 --> 00:05:52,049
Let's go.

68
00:05:52,489 --> 00:05:53,950
I like how you cut to the chase.

69
00:05:57,731 --> 00:05:58,731
Mistress Frieren.

70
00:05:59,912 --> 00:06:00,912
It's Mr. Stark.

71
00:06:04,757 --> 00:06:05,778
That didn't take long.

72
00:06:06,879 --> 00:06:08,741
Any chance you can temporarily wake him?

73
00:06:09,742 --> 00:06:11,464
I told you I don't have the proper tools.

74
00:06:11,924 --> 00:06:14,067
As is, I could only keep
him up for five seconds.

75
00:06:14,627 --> 00:06:15,908
That's practically nothing.

76
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:19,252
In any case, looks like we should hurry.

77
00:06:42,029 --> 00:06:43,190
Fern's out cold, too.

78
00:06:43,650 --> 00:06:45,431
So much for her taking a little break.

79
00:06:46,331 --> 00:06:47,968
We've lost half of our manpower.

80
00:06:47,992 --> 00:06:50,854
Our odds are starting to look grim.

81
00:06:54,116 --> 00:06:55,116
I put up a barrier.

82
00:06:55,637 --> 00:06:56,837
We'll hide them here for now.

83
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,240
We're almost there.

84
00:07:03,821 --> 00:07:05,322
I can sense it.

85
00:07:05,742 --> 00:07:06,742
Good.

86
00:07:07,103 --> 00:07:10,145
Say, Sein, wake me when
the monster shows up.

87
00:07:11,585 --> 00:07:13,425
I don't want you fighting
that creature alone.

88
00:07:14,246 --> 00:07:16,046
I promise you now that I shall defeat it.

89
00:07:16,586 --> 00:07:17,626
Were you not listening?

90
00:07:17,946 --> 00:07:21,747
I can only give you... Frieren?

91
00:07:24,467 --> 00:07:26,268
You can't defeat it in five seconds.

92
00:07:35,509 --> 00:07:36,509
So be it.

93
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:38,450
I have battle magic too.

94
00:07:57,827 --> 00:07:59,728
It's a subspecies of chaos flower.

95
00:08:00,508 --> 00:08:02,529
It must be feeding off
the sleeping villagers.

96
00:08:04,329 --> 00:08:09,571
It'll sap their mana
away until it kills them.

97
00:08:12,553 --> 00:08:17,234
Chaos flowers are known to merge with the
local flora and branch off into new variations.

98
00:08:20,075 --> 00:08:21,075
Almost mirror-like.

99
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:27,118
Though they come in different shapes and sizes,
they all have the same weak spot at their core.

100
00:08:30,135 --> 00:08:31,356
Three Spears of the Goddess!

101
00:08:40,540 --> 00:08:41,457
What was that about?

102
00:08:41,481 --> 00:08:45,643
I didn't think the blasted
thing would reflect my magic.

103
00:08:47,103 --> 00:08:52,526
Unless I land a direct hit on the core, the leaves
can deflect whatever I throw at it in any direction.

104
00:08:54,127 --> 00:08:55,928
If I'm not careful, it could hit Frieren.

105
00:08:59,022 --> 00:08:59,442
Damn it!

106
00:08:59,762 --> 00:09:01,122
This can only get worse from here.

107
00:09:01,563 --> 00:09:03,323
Should I heed the elf's
orders and wake her?

108
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:05,585
She's the mage from the Party of Heroes.

109
00:09:06,165 --> 00:09:11,267
If a spell of hers were deflected, it would destroy
not only the forest, but the entire village with it.

110
00:09:13,688 --> 00:09:15,129
I'd only have five seconds.

111
00:09:15,649 --> 00:09:17,150
That's not enough time to explain.

112
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:22,852
As sharp as Frieren is, we haven't had time to develop
any kind of shared trust or mutual understanding.

113
00:09:23,332 --> 00:09:24,753
I can't even get a read on her.

114
00:09:25,113 --> 00:09:26,714
What goes on in that ancient head?

115
00:09:28,978 --> 00:09:29,978
That's right.

116
00:09:30,279 --> 00:09:34,081
You might find it hard to believe,
but I can never tell what she's thinking.

117
00:09:35,101 --> 00:09:36,742
Shared trust is a luxury.

118
00:09:37,062 --> 00:09:39,284
As in, it's not something adventurers need.

119
00:09:39,544 --> 00:09:41,225
Nothing has to be unspoken.

120
00:09:41,985 --> 00:09:47,268
I know this because my companion Frieren was
terrible at cultivating mutual understanding.

121
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:53,111
Since intent couldn't be assured with a look
or a touch, I decided I would trust her words.

122
00:09:54,452 --> 00:09:58,094
For example, she swore to us all
that she would defeat the Demon King.

123
00:09:59,187 --> 00:10:01,669
Though it was a bold
claim, I chose to believe her.

124
00:10:03,110 --> 00:10:04,271
Trust her words, huh?

125
00:10:11,396 --> 00:10:13,577
I don't want you fighting
that creature on your own.

126
00:10:13,937 --> 00:10:15,919
I promise you now that I shall defeat it.

127
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:20,502
That face didn't look
ready to defeat anything.

128
00:10:21,103 --> 00:10:22,760
Whatever happens, don't blame me!

129
00:10:22,784 --> 00:10:24,965
A Wickeding Spell!

130
00:10:28,952 --> 00:10:29,493
Frieren!

131
00:10:29,773 --> 00:10:30,773
Only the core!

132
00:10:52,073 --> 00:10:53,073
Done.

133
00:10:53,434 --> 00:10:54,434
Simple enough.

134
00:11:10,484 --> 00:11:11,644
Thank you very much.

135
00:11:12,865 --> 00:11:14,525
I won't forget what you've done for us.

136
00:11:15,206 --> 00:11:15,786
It's nothing.

137
00:11:16,066 --> 00:11:17,786
I can assure you we didn't do much, ma'am.

138
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:19,667
Hush now.

139
00:11:20,327 --> 00:11:22,508
I've never been happier
to have my sleep disturbed.

140
00:11:28,594 --> 00:11:31,057
I knew our flower was
the type that reflects magic.

141
00:11:31,638 --> 00:11:33,580
I recognized it the moment you woke me up.

142
00:11:34,601 --> 00:11:37,405
There's no question that
you're an incredible mage.

143
00:11:38,085 --> 00:11:41,289
That might be the case, but you're
the reason we made it out of there alive.

144
00:11:42,551 --> 00:11:43,652
Thank you very much, Sein.

145
00:11:57,532 --> 00:12:00,093
That lady from the village sure was pretty.

146
00:12:00,753 --> 00:12:02,094
You're still on that?

147
00:12:04,735 --> 00:12:05,976
So that's Foresh, huh?

148
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:09,877
More importantly, it's the
midpoint in our journey to Oyserst.

149
00:12:11,038 --> 00:12:12,455
We're only halfway there?

150
00:12:12,479 --> 00:12:14,860
This really is a long journey.

151
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:18,681
While we're here, let's drop
in and replenish our supplies.

152
00:12:18,861 --> 00:12:19,962
Um, Mistress Frieren?

153
00:12:21,002 --> 00:12:24,384
I hate to be the bearer of bad
news, but our funds are-Hey!

154
00:12:24,924 --> 00:12:25,924
You there.

155
00:12:26,165 --> 00:12:27,165
What now?

156
00:12:30,128 --> 00:12:31,589
That looks like a noble's carriage.

157
00:12:33,249 --> 00:12:34,249
Huh?

158
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:35,870
Excuse you!

159
00:12:36,051 --> 00:12:37,051
What is going on?!

160
00:12:37,431 --> 00:12:38,492
He has a good physique.

161
00:12:38,872 --> 00:12:40,153
His looks aren't bad either.

162
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:41,233
Get in.

163
00:12:41,734 --> 00:12:42,914
I'll take you to my mansion.

164
00:12:44,155 --> 00:12:47,076
Does anybody care to explain?!

165
00:12:53,439 --> 00:12:54,439
Who are you, lad?

166
00:12:55,260 --> 00:12:56,300
The name is Stark.

167
00:12:56,601 --> 00:12:57,601
Lord Ordon, sir.

168
00:12:57,961 --> 00:12:59,442
You cannot hold us without reason.

169
00:13:00,006 --> 00:13:01,547
I need no introduction, I see.

170
00:13:02,207 --> 00:13:06,209
This mansion is home to the Ordens, one of the
three great families of the Northern Lands.

171
00:13:07,089 --> 00:13:09,250
Your grandfather, he was pushy too.

172
00:13:09,770 --> 00:13:14,612
I don't know what nonsense you're trying to
engage me in, but I'm preoccupied at the moment.

173
00:13:14,913 --> 00:13:16,373
Stark and I need to have a word.

174
00:13:16,673 --> 00:13:18,974
If you can talk to my
warrior, you can talk to me.

175
00:13:21,275 --> 00:13:22,275
Tell me, Stark.

176
00:13:22,536 --> 00:13:24,937
Do you need your mommy's
permission to have a conversation?

177
00:13:25,857 --> 00:13:27,058
Come on, don't fight.

178
00:13:28,137 --> 00:13:30,859
I have a job for you,
and I will pay you well.

179
00:13:31,399 --> 00:13:32,399
No, no chance.

180
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:33,580
We're leaving, Stark.

181
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,121
Mistress Frieren.

182
00:13:40,104 --> 00:13:41,144
What's with the copper?

183
00:13:41,925 --> 00:13:43,606
That's the remainder of our funds.

184
00:13:46,067 --> 00:13:48,549
I suppose that at the very
least we can hear you out.

185
00:13:49,169 --> 00:13:50,169
Akimi.

186
00:13:54,032 --> 00:13:56,173
So, Stark, from where do you hail?

187
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,901
I'm from a warrior village
in the Klee region, sir.

188
00:14:00,682 --> 00:14:01,682
I know the place.

189
00:14:02,143 --> 00:14:04,744
My family line originates
from the very same region.

190
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:11,768
My eldest son, Wirt.

191
00:14:13,169 --> 00:14:16,190
He is a hero of this city,
and the heir to my title.

192
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,112
He looks like you, Mr. Stark.

193
00:14:20,033 --> 00:14:21,033
Indeed he does.

194
00:14:21,814 --> 00:14:25,956
If we changed you and cleaned you up, only a
close family member could discern the difference.

195
00:14:26,822 --> 00:14:29,544
I have a feeling that's going
to play into your job offer.

196
00:14:30,985 --> 00:14:34,728
About a month ago now, we took a
vast army of demons on head-to-head.

197
00:14:35,328 --> 00:14:37,470
My son lost his life on the battlefield.

198
00:14:38,111 --> 00:14:40,152
He and the enemy
commander killed each other.

199
00:14:41,673 --> 00:14:46,237
The only silver lining, if you could call it as
much, is that it happened in a large-scale melee.

200
00:14:47,718 --> 00:14:49,039
Very few know he's dead.

201
00:14:49,899 --> 00:14:53,082
Gabel is aware, as well as
some of my most trusted men.

202
00:14:57,105 --> 00:14:59,406
So what is it that you're
planning to make Stark do?

203
00:15:02,508 --> 00:15:06,630
Voresh is a powerful fortress city,
a key player in this region's defense.

204
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:11,412
Until we can rebuild the forces we
lost, we can't allow morale to slip.

205
00:15:12,813 --> 00:15:15,354
So you want to cover up
your son's death until then.

206
00:15:16,535 --> 00:15:21,418
Three months from now, all of the area's most
influential figures will gather at a soiree.

207
00:15:21,938 --> 00:15:24,139
We'll show them there
that Wirt is alive and well.

208
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,320
And our reward?

209
00:15:26,596 --> 00:15:28,617
I will give you ten Strahl gold coins.

210
00:15:29,457 --> 00:15:32,258
That would be three meals a
day for an entire year, plus snacks.

211
00:15:32,558 --> 00:15:33,638
Sweeten it with a grimoire.

212
00:15:34,358 --> 00:15:37,059
You can have your pick of the
library after our work is done.

213
00:15:37,599 --> 00:15:38,259
One problem.

214
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:39,479
I'm not your guy.

215
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,880
Folks aren't gonna miss
the big scar on my forehead.

216
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:46,061
The people believe Wirt is currently
recovering from damage taken in combat.

217
00:15:46,862 --> 00:15:49,702
That's an honorable battle scar.

218
00:15:51,563 --> 00:15:53,603
Mr. Stark, we need the money.

219
00:15:54,444 --> 00:15:55,444
More pathetic.

220
00:15:56,512 --> 00:15:59,335
Gabel, I leave the boys'
etiquette training to you.

221
00:16:26,504 --> 00:16:29,305
Mr. Stark, how is etiquette
training coming along?

222
00:16:29,945 --> 00:16:31,245
It's slowly killing me.

223
00:16:39,727 --> 00:16:40,727
What do you think?

224
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:43,668
Doesn't suit you.

225
00:16:44,188 --> 00:16:45,188
Typical.

226
00:16:45,968 --> 00:16:47,829
Well, my lady, I must get some air.

227
00:16:56,377 --> 00:16:57,377
Lord Ordon.

228
00:16:59,858 --> 00:17:02,399
Haven't I told you a hundred
times to call me father?

229
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:05,141
You never know whose
prying eyes could be upon us.

230
00:17:05,781 --> 00:17:07,321
Aren't you being a little bit cold?

231
00:17:08,622 --> 00:17:11,423
It's only been two months since
your actual son passed away.

232
00:17:12,043 --> 00:17:15,125
All that I've done has been in
accordance with my son's final wishes.

233
00:17:15,985 --> 00:17:17,666
I even had another double prepared.

234
00:17:19,106 --> 00:17:21,106
He didn't look as much
like him as you do, though.

235
00:17:23,118 --> 00:17:26,421
Trust me, it's not as if I
enjoy this cruel charade.

236
00:17:29,163 --> 00:17:30,504
But it's what my son wanted.

237
00:17:32,446 --> 00:17:33,667
So cooperate, would you?

238
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:42,434
You're not too big on
the people skills, huh?

239
00:17:43,956 --> 00:17:44,616
Stand tall.

240
00:17:44,936 --> 00:17:46,178
Don't shrink yourself, Mut.

241
00:17:46,978 --> 00:17:47,978
Yes, father, of course.

242
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,922
That's my second son, Mut.

243
00:17:51,633 --> 00:17:55,035
Despite the fact he's to be my heir
now, he shows little improvement.

244
00:17:55,956 --> 00:17:57,577
Then, of course, there's your brother.

245
00:17:58,097 --> 00:17:59,358
Our family's great shame.

246
00:18:04,181 --> 00:18:06,442
Having skill with a sword
affects one's posture.

247
00:18:07,123 --> 00:18:09,304
I shall teach you the
technique of the Orden family.

248
00:18:14,988 --> 00:18:15,988
What's wrong?

249
00:18:21,942 --> 00:18:22,942
It's all right.

250
00:18:23,003 --> 00:18:24,003
Take deep breaths.

251
00:18:26,044 --> 00:18:27,045
This isn't your village.

252
00:18:27,085 --> 00:18:28,225
You're safe to learn here.

253
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:34,028
I realize he's still a kid, but
what do you think of Moot?

254
00:18:34,829 --> 00:18:36,530
He doesn't have his brother's talent.

255
00:18:38,471 --> 00:18:39,571
But he's a hard worker.

256
00:18:40,932 --> 00:18:43,573
Time and effort are
investments that always pay off.

257
00:18:44,634 --> 00:18:47,755
Once he's grown, he'll be a far
stronger knight than I ever was.

258
00:18:48,476 --> 00:18:49,476
Gotcha.

259
00:18:50,732 --> 00:18:52,734
You should really tell
that to Moot instead of me.

260
00:18:53,374 --> 00:18:54,475
I tell him all the time.

261
00:18:55,375 --> 00:18:57,957
Now it's gone to his head
and he refuses to get better.

262
00:19:00,059 --> 00:19:01,699
That's a whole different kind of problem.

263
00:19:02,821 --> 00:19:03,821
Huh?

264
00:19:04,302 --> 00:19:06,744
You're saying I have to learn
all that etiquette stuff too?

265
00:19:07,124 --> 00:19:08,405
Well, it is a soiree.

266
00:19:08,745 --> 00:19:12,568
Do you really expect a man of his age
to attend such a function on his own?

267
00:19:14,329 --> 00:19:17,131
I suppose his mommy could
always escort him instead.

268
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,133
Good luck, Fern.

269
00:19:51,313 --> 00:19:56,595
This past month has been
nothing short of torture.

270
00:19:57,955 --> 00:19:59,516
But anything for the money, right?

271
00:20:00,476 --> 00:20:01,737
I'm sorry about all that.

272
00:20:11,721 --> 00:20:13,421
We've been practicing this for ages.

273
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:14,921
We might as well.

274
00:20:16,782 --> 00:20:18,363
It still doesn't suit you, you know.

275
00:21:29,008 --> 00:21:30,288
Would you like to dance as well?

276
00:21:31,709 --> 00:21:32,710
I'd like to eat.

277
00:21:35,431 --> 00:21:36,431
Fair enough.

278
00:21:41,193 --> 00:21:45,454
If not for this damn injury, I would
have been in the vanguard alongside him.

279
00:21:46,974 --> 00:21:48,855
Perhaps then Wirt would still be with us.

280
00:21:49,996 --> 00:21:50,996
M'lord.

281
00:21:55,377 --> 00:21:57,198
It looks like the soiree's wrapping up.

282
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:01,514
You've completed your work with us.

283
00:22:02,195 --> 00:22:04,916
Gabel, see to it Frieren gets her reward.

284
00:22:13,802 --> 00:22:18,306
I've found you're far more powerful a
warrior than you appear at first glance.

285
00:22:19,166 --> 00:22:20,627
If you ever need a place to stay

286
00:22:20,787 --> 00:22:22,909
I'm sorry, sir, but I can't replace your son.

287
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:25,270
Of course you can't.

288
00:22:26,551 --> 00:22:29,073
No more than I could
ever replace your father.

289
00:22:30,439 --> 00:22:32,140
But you don't have a home to return to.

290
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:36,541
The warrior village of the Klee
region was destroyed by demons.

291
00:22:37,241 --> 00:22:38,382
I'm certain of that much.

292
00:22:41,022 --> 00:22:42,883
My son and I parted ways in anger.

293
00:22:44,083 --> 00:22:45,804
All due to some petty argument.

294
00:22:47,064 --> 00:22:51,126
I worked myself into a fit of rage and told
him I never wanted to see his face again.

295
00:22:53,347 --> 00:22:54,647
I didn't mean one bit of it.

296
00:22:59,245 --> 00:23:02,607
When I first came upon you,
I mistook you for a miracle.

297
00:23:06,409 --> 00:23:08,490
That's all the more
reason I can't stay here.

298
00:23:10,591 --> 00:23:15,254
I said things I didn't mean and parted in
anger, too, with the man who raised me.

299
00:23:16,835 --> 00:23:21,177
So now, my hope is to make things right
by bringing him back stories of my travels.

300
00:23:23,998 --> 00:23:24,998
I wish you well.

301
00:23:29,127 --> 00:23:33,470
Hmm... Should I rule out
Grimoire Y or Grimoire Z?

302
00:23:34,190 --> 00:23:37,232
Mistress Frieren, you've
been deciding for half a day.

303
00:23:38,553 --> 00:23:40,054
You're distressing Mr. Gobel.

304
00:23:41,054 --> 00:23:42,054
Please hurry.

305
00:23:43,115 --> 00:23:45,537
Look, you trained the
poor man's life force.

306
00:23:46,917 --> 00:23:50,157
They say it'll still be some time before
their troops are back to what they were.

307
00:23:54,242 --> 00:23:55,242
What's up?

308
00:23:57,704 --> 00:23:58,704
Nothing.

309
00:24:02,540 --> 00:24:07,162
At the very least, he won't
have to worry about his heir.

310
00:24:09,723 --> 00:24:17,723
Forgotten heroes, huh?

311
00:24:22,049 --> 00:24:23,685
They're forgotten heroes.

312
00:24:23,709 --> 00:24:24,546
More like degraded.

313
00:24:24,570 --> 00:24:26,010
No one knows their names.

314
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:27,731
Humans develop quickly.

315
00:24:28,131 --> 00:24:29,472
He's a long-lived friend of mine.

